Check Vault Logs

# View service logs
sudo journalctl -u vault -f

# View specific time range
sudo journalctl -u vault --since "1 hour ago"

-----------------------------------------------

Common Issues
Vault is Sealed

vault operator unseal <key-1>
vault operator unseal <key-2>
vault operator unseal <key-3>

----------------------------------------------

Permission Denied

# Check file permissions
ls -la /opt/vault/data
ls -la /etc/vault.d

# Fix if needed
sudo chown -R vault:vault /opt/vault/data /etc/vault.d

-----------------------------------------------

* Security Considerations
For Production Deployments

1. Enable TLS: Never run production Vault without TLS
2. Use External Storage: Consider Consul, etcd, or cloud storage
3. Enable mlock: Set disable_mlock = false
4. Secure Unseal Keys: Use separate key custodians
5. Regular Backups: Implement automated backup strategy
6. Audit Logging: Enable and monitor audit logs
7. Network Isolation: Run Vault in isolated network segment
8. Auto-Unseal: Consider using cloud KMS for auto-unsealing

TLS Configuration Example

# hcl

listener "tcp" {
  address       = "0.0.0.0:8200"
  tls_cert_file = "/etc/vault.d/vault.crt"
  tls_key_file  = "/etc/vault.d/vault.key"
}

